					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>Sefer Livnat ha-sapir, on Genesis and Leviticus.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="1r" to="430v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Livnat ha-sapir</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">לבנת הספיר</title>
							<note>
								<p>See further <ref target="Felix_1991" type="page">1-6</ref>.</p>
								<p>Folios 226r-231v contain a commentary on Hosea, partially written in a different hand (folios 230-231).</p>
								<p>The commentary on Genesis begins on folio 4r; on Leviticus, folio 232r; Tosafot on the pericope Tsaṿ and others of Leviticus, folio 416v.</p>
								<p>There are a number of lacunae in the extant parts, e.g., at the end of folio 63 and 200 (marked by the scribe).</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/305195011">Angelino, Josef</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/305195011">אנג'לט, יוסף</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>430 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>215</height>
										<width>155</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>155</height>
										<width>105</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>430 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and 2 at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p> 	Quires of mostly 12 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="20" writtenLines="20">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Initial words in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Oriental semi-cursive script of the 16th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="230r" to="231v"/> due to a different hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 430r contains notes in a late Italian hand on certain features of the manuscript.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Luigi da Bologna</name>, a converted Jew working for the Inquisition as censor (active 1590-1609): inscribed with his name as censor: 'Visto per mi F. Luigi da Bologna del 1600' (folio 429v). See <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">104</ref>, and appendix § 112-117. </p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (active 1600-1624): inscribed with his name, 1619 (folio 428v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>, and appendix § 80-84. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM/BL in-house.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Libnath Has-Sappir. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional MS. 27,000.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
					</physDesc>
